content: The analysis revealed that view links, such as https://drive.google.com/file/d/[FILE_ID]/view?usp=sharing, were more promising for extracting text, as they render the file content in the browser, potentially within HTML tags like <div> or <pre>. However, the query’s effectiveness depended on its specificity, with natural language queries like “full content of the file” sometimes returning summaries rather than the entire text, which, given the user’s note that the first file’s summary was the document, might be sufficient. Download links, while theoretically providing raw text, were less effective, as the “Browse Page” action couldn’t parse the download prompt’s HTML for readable text.
